    "Body": " Do you want to provide a significant impetus to your career? Do you want to play a relevant role in a Leader Consulting Company? Do you want to participate to a daily great experience of Digital Transformation in Capgemini? ? Take your Chance, Join Capgemini Team, Go on this important travel! ? Transformation Consulting is looking for: ? Operations Transformation Consultant/Senior Consultant ? You will be part of the Transformation Consulting, the Business Unit of Capgemini Italy, focused on Digital Innovation, Consulting and Transformation. At Capgemini Transformation Consulting we bring to life what\u2019s next for our clients. The mission of Operations Transformation is to assist customers to respond to market complexity driving them through the transformation of their operations optimizing supply chains, manufacturing, procurement and their underlying processes reinventing product engineering, manufacturing and physical asset management exploiting robotics, AI, lean, deep manufacturing expertise and digital technology applications by analyzing consolidated practices and questioning them in a perspective of complete transformation for continuous and disruptive improvement. Passport Your missions, serving our customers, will maximize the contributions into the operations transformation with the support of Artificial Intelligence, Blockchain, Machine Learning, BPA, RPA and all Digital technologies. In charge of a Transformation Project, you will lead the realization of the work from A to Z. Manage people and support junior profile in their daily activities aligned with the project strategy Support and conduct analysis and interviews / customer workshops, then formulate optimization levers and recommendations designing scenarios Coordinate and participate to all phases of implementation of operational transformation in close collaboration with the customer and all the stakeholders Support activities of Manager and Principle Understands how to construct and gain agreement for business cases Build a stable, trusted and long-term relationship with the client Opens new discussions and builds new opportunities with clients Actively support sales and territory teams to position and deliver large, transformational opportunities generating revenues Some example of mission: Participate in transformation projects that require only partial revolution or revision of operations by defining the transformation strategy and designing the transformation roadmap Analyze operational processes throughout the life cycle of products/services offered by customers and map them for improvement Propose and discuss innovative and technological end-to-end solutions taking into account industry 4.0 paradigms through the study of consolidated use cases or thinking about new addressing client business issues and objectives using a combination of standardized and customized services. Design use cases that portray the proposed solutions and assess the impact on processes by identifying the risks and opportunities of the different solutions Shapes approach to identifying and managing risks and assumptions and for realizing benefits at a program level Education & Experience ? Strong experience of 1-4 or several years in Financial services or manufacturing markets Proven experience in process analysis according the most important international techniques and standard (e.g. BPM, IDEF) Proven experience in lean or world class manufacturing standard in operation excellence projects Proven experience in operations transformation following all the phases of digital transformation projects (e.g. for example introduction of ERP, TMS, Policy management system) Advanced operational analysis capabilities through the use of consolidated tools and techniques Ability to work constructively in a team by fostering a collaborative climate and leveraging team skills Knowledge and interest in all industrial and service sectors Strong inclination towards the use of technologies such as analytics, machine learning, Artificial intelligence, RPA, BPA, etc. Excellent communication and interpersonal skills that foster relationship building. Experience of 2-5 years in consulting firms in operations and strategy or in industrial business company Ability to represent firm with senior client executives ? ? Candidate profile Entrepreneur and enthusiastic, bilingual English and mobile, you are ready to implement your open-mindedness and your ability to work as a team in the service of our customers. Endowed with a strong intellectual curiosity and a great capacity of adaptation, you wish to integrate a motivating professional environment where you will fully value your sense of the results, your qualities of analysis and mobilization of teams. ? People Matter, Results Count What sets us apart is exactly what defines us. Our talents, our people pursue the objectives with enthusiasm and team spirit, aware of being able to reach them because they are supported by a reality that does not set limits to growth. Honesty, initiative and fun are our Key Words: these are the values \u200b\u200bthat make us the first choice for our customers and an excellent opportunity for growth for each talent. We hire qualified and valuable people without distinction of sex, race, disability, age, sexual orientation, religion or belief, marital status accompanying our people in the way of parenting. We promote an inclusive culture that allows everyone to show their full potential and enjoy a satisfying career. Our flexible benefits Policy and our Policies in general promote a lifestyle based on work life balance. Our mission is to employ, develop and retain the best people to provide innovative solutions to our customers. We honor our commitments, paying attention to the resources belonging to protected categories, pursuant to articles 1 and 18 of the law 68 of '99. Personal data will be processed in accordance with the provisions contained in the 2016/679 EU regulation. ? ? ? ? ? ? Please, read our Privacy Policy: http://capgemini.hrweb.it/candidatura.php?id_an=231802 ", 
